<subSubSection id="3CCAF8D47591E5AE45818ADDAFB23720" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="4DEAD89CCBD910652427188F62BA650A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0EFE1680C0FE3EBF80F9B12372BD2F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
15.0-70.0 cm tall, erect or spreading. Stem pubescent in lower part, scabrous, glabrous but with sessile glands in upper part; with 8-12(-20) distinct internodes, the uppermost internode (3.0-)4.0-6.0(-7.0) cm long and obviously longer than the next upper internode. Basal leaves linear or oblanceolate 1.0-4.0 
<normalizedToken id="D921604E550D0C95E0842A9049ECD497" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.0-4.0 mm, pubescent. Cauline leaves linear 10.0-30.0
<normalizedToken id="2238DF631A77A195608B9CC153F9E3F3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.0-3.0 mm, pubescent. Calyx 9.0-14.0 mm long, campanulate at anthesis and clavate in fruit, pubescent; teeth unequal; shorter ones 2.0-3.0 mm, lanceolate, acuminate; longer ones 2.0-4.0 mm, lanceolate, acuminate; marginal hairs long (longer than 0.5 mm), dense. Inflorescence non-divaricate, branch axile (much) less than 90°. Petal claws 4.0-7.5 mm long, ciliate; limbs 5.0-6.5 mm long, bifid, upper-surface white or pink, lobes oblong, petal limbs cleft to middle or more; coronal scales 0.8-1.4 mm long, ovate, apex dentate or erose. Anthophore 3.0-5.0 mm long, densely puberulent. Anthers exserted; filaments 6.0-9.0 mm long, sometimes pubescent. Styles exserted. First pedicel 1.0-3.0 cm in flower, 1.0-4.0 cm in fruit, erect, glabrous, apex antrorse. Capsule 6.0-7.0 mm long, oblong, fragile, opaque. Seeds 0.6-1.0 mm wide, 0.4-0.8 mm high, testa smooth or papillate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E30ED9E060CD3C4C5A793546171852F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A48AE351B4CBE20F3CB9C7CE4798337E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87F29C15F4B6D67E982832A1890CD4F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
South Central Turkey, W and N Syria (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="30FDAB1301AD557EA17F2EDA6C1C1085" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of S. sect. Arenosae. Each color code corresponds to one taxon: A S. arenosa B S. austroiranica C S. chaetodonta D S. exsudans E S. georgievskyi F S. leyseroides G S. linearis H S. microsperma subsp. cypria I S. microsperma subsp. maritima J S. microsperma subsp. microsperma K S. microsperma subsp. modesta L S. striata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.159.51500.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447291" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7</figureCitation>
). Specimens from near the border between Iraq and Iran with ciliate petal claws but in other characteristics resembling 
<taxonomicName id="948E72FFF995015D179A37BBC8E68E26" genus="S." lsidName="S. chaetodonta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="chaetodonta">
<emphasis id="A5B1B875D628E64599509D8F5984E2B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. chaetodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been suggested to be of hybrid origin (
<bibRefCitation id="676B07D9A85492669E35EE8DB57A79E6" author="Melzheimer, V" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="341 - 508" refId="B35" refString="Melzheimer, V, 1988. Silene L. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora des iranischen hochlandes und der umrahmenden Gebirge (Persien, Afghanistan, Teile von West-Pakistan, Nord-Iraq, Azerbaidjan, Turkmenistan)): Caryophyllaceae II, Vol. 163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 341 - 508" title="Silene L." volumeTitle="Flora des iranischen hochlandes und der umrahmenden Gebirge (Persien, Afghanistan, Teile von West-Pakistan, Nord-Iraq, Azerbaidjan, Turkmenistan )): Caryophyllaceae II, Vol." year="1988">Melzheimer 1988</bibRefCitation>
) and deserve closer investigation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="61712AD2059C20E6743477AF6769D35A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="610158B496E79D6BECB34626351638B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77D01550FEE8DB6D26D62BD7982B3A43" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The stem often has a larger number of internodes than other taxa in the section, sometimes as many as 20, although more often up to 12 clearly separated, distinct stem internodes. The middle internodes are shorter than or up to two (three) times the length of the subtending pair of leaves (the basalmost nodes are very short for all species). This gives this taxon a 
<normalizedToken id="955A59FCE90699984B9C6E28ECCC7DFD" originalValue="“leafy”">&quot;leafy&quot;</normalizedToken>
appearance, reinforced by many branches and leafy shoots in leaf axils. The uppermost axillary branches are often opposite. This taxon is very variable, but is recognized by the many internodes, the ciliate petal claws and the small mamillae on the seeds.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AAB74BBD635A6D23DFED6582841010B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="A7369493BCD8D848FBC6409FF1876170" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene cassia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cassia">
<emphasis id="33F979B4E85C23379B993A910C4F79A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene cassia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the name used for white flowered variants according to 
<bibRefCitation id="E22E5334BB8931D59A0F826936AC454E" author="Coode, MJE" editor="Davis, PH" journalOrPublisher="2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="179 - 242" refId="B14" refString="Coode, MJE, Cullen, J, 1967. Silene L. In: Davis, PH, Ed., Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, Vol. 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh: 179 - 242" title="Silene L." volumeTitle="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, Vol." year="1967">Coode and Cullen (1967)</bibRefCitation>
. It is possible that the name 
<taxonomicName id="38E42BBEB41B478775C55C5733F82E27" genus="S." lsidName="S. ehrenbergiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ehrenbergiana">
<emphasis id="96BAAF42FF02FF1961779260A499648C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. ehrenbergiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rohrb. [in Bot. Zeitung (Berlin) 25: 83. 1867. - Type: &quot;Bei Fakra (?) in Syrien im Juni&quot; Ehrenberg, B destroyed?] is associated with this taxon, but we have not been able to confirm this.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CF3A1AE68F8D82D387475EEC4D97DC3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph id="405C9811DB55133BC8F954F6AA468375" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BA5B6022E40528813677BE5A4A98504" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Many authors have used the name 
<taxonomicName id="D23402D4DF17E792B7077F5365BD04B3" genus="S." lsidName="S. kotschyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="B9646A79A64C4A4235750781A78EA8ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss. for this species (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="C0521A85A1C3DF80A2B7CE187C3BB1D5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.20323" author="Boissier, E" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B5" refString="Boissier, E, 1867. Flora Orientalis: sive, Enumeratio plantarum in Oriente a Graecia et Aegypto ad Indiae fines hucusque observatarum, Vol. 1. apud H. Georg, Basileae &amp; Geneve, 1-1017. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.20323" title="Flora Orientalis: sive, Enumeratio plantarum in Oriente a Graecia et Aegypto ad Indiae fines hucusque observatarum, Vol. 1. apud H. Georg, Basileae &amp; Geneve, 1 - 1017." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.20323" year="1867">Boissier 1867</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DF49C66E2E5A528B2A4381C3A9F8EFB2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1896.tb00695.x" author="Williams, FN" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="B64" refString="Williams, FN, 1896. A revision of the genus Silene L. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 32 (220-227): 1 - 196, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1896.tb00695.x" title="A revision of the genus Silene L." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1896.tb00695.x" volume="32" year="1896">Williams 1896</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="84AE5AF207358AB6A909A5D9D018CCED" author="Post, GE" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B49" refString="Post, GE, 1932. Flora of Syria, Palestine and Sinai (ed. 2). Ripol Klassik, Beirut, 1-639." title="Flora of Syria, Palestine and Sinai (ed. 2). Ripol Klassik, Beirut, 1 - 639." year="1932">Post 1932</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="94DA2B7C97D639AD17493B9324C828C8" author="Chowdhuri, PK" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="221 - 278" refId="B13" refString="Chowdhuri, PK, 1957. Studies in the genus Silene. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 22: 221 - 278" title="Studies in the genus Silene." volume="22" year="1957">Chowdhuri 1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="27ED36133D2F5E5A3F0E19E612B2FBA3" author="Mouterde, P" journalOrPublisher="163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B37" refString="Mouterde, P, 1966. Nouvelle Flore du Liban et de la Syrie. Vol. 1. Ed. de l'imprimerie catholique, Beyrouth, 1-563." title="Nouvelle Flore du Liban et de la Syrie. Vol. 1. Ed. de l'imprimerie catholique, Beyrouth, 1 - 563." year="1966">Mouterde 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="618B311A98D09D0CBABA360DEDA98D2E" author="Coode, MJE" editor="Davis, PH" journalOrPublisher="2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="179 - 242" refId="B14" refString="Coode, MJE, Cullen, J, 1967. Silene L. In: Davis, PH, Ed., Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, Vol. 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh: 179 - 242" title="Silene L." volumeTitle="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, Vol." year="1967">Coode and Cullen 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A680536AACEB2081E942A99A386342F6" author="Meikle, RD" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B34" refString="Meikle, RD, 1977. Flora of Cyprus, Vol. 1. Bentham-Moxon Trust, Kew, 1-832." title="Flora of Cyprus, Vol. 1. Bentham-Moxon Trust, Kew, 1 - 832." year="1977">Meikle 1977</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="7AE2C2E10B1C8503F9D1BABE41352214" author="Melzheimer, V" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="341 - 508" refId="B35" refString="Melzheimer, V, 1988. Silene L. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora des iranischen hochlandes und der umrahmenden Gebirge (Persien, Afghanistan, Teile von West-Pakistan, Nord-Iraq, Azerbaidjan, Turkmenistan)): Caryophyllaceae II, Vol. 163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 341 - 508" title="Silene L." volumeTitle="Flora des iranischen hochlandes und der umrahmenden Gebirge (Persien, Afghanistan, Teile von West-Pakistan, Nord-Iraq, Azerbaidjan, Turkmenistan )): Caryophyllaceae II, Vol." year="1988">Melzheimer (1988)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="6DD5EF21184F6C74B3CB4734766608E7" genus="S." lsidName="S. kotschyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="538530D8FA0A7C17F4B33AF3DA13E026" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss. as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="D218BF9F01B1CF2C44EB61F060C0FCFF" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="AF1AF8281B51884E973C992A3771B3F4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fenzl. We have not been able to find any type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="35B0E36E7A73DEA31514683E8DFEF999" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="9F6756A1D0E1F1A882D1689BC54C9CC1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Fenzl noted 
<emphasis id="E2F874D3BBE0AF93BC5F4ACA7C1A9CBE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">specimen unicum</emphasis>
in the protologue, so it is possible that the only type material has been destroyed during the Second World War bombings of Berlin. The description made by Fenzl is short and unspecific and fits any species in 
<taxonomicName id="CAB5490B6759E644773931E99AE5E16B" genus="S." lsidName="S. subsp. sect." pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="section" section="Arenosae" species="microsperma" subSpecies="sect.">S. sect. Arenosae</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="104CF584540D8F76BFB75A115F789B63" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.15462" author="Rohrbach, P" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B54" refString="Rohrbach, P, 1868. Monographie der Gattung Silene. W. Engelmann, Leipzig, 1-249. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.15462" title="Monographie der Gattung Silene. W. Engelmann, Leipzig, 1 - 249." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.15462" year="1868">Rohrbach (1868)</bibRefCitation>
used the name 
<taxonomicName id="9D5516B65ED99A0B2921784BB9FE1A6E" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="5EDB6412B71CE81ED260F5B237B2A6A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fenzl and listed 
<taxonomicName id="6E59AC7CBCB141677368653DD95398CD" genus="S." lsidName="S. kotschyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="B1E9F224A473474E5286387B1507D481" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss. as a synonym, and it is likely that he had seen the specimen cited by Fenzl. 
<bibRefCitation id="216EA438C1046FBC28ACEA8F1282C741" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4109339" author="Burtt, BL" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="333 - 352" refId="B9" refString="Burtt, BL, Lewis, P, 1952. On the Flora of Kuweit: II. Kew Bulletin 7 (3): 333 - 352, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4109339" title="On the Flora of Kuweit: II." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4109339" volume="7" year="1952">Burtt and Lewis (1952)</bibRefCitation>
use the name 
<taxonomicName id="AC061790BAE641C6826C301082B7B475" genus="S." lsidName="S. kotschyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="930B86E3F423C02AFF234EC137A8E8F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss., but they cited the publication year as 1842, the same as for 
<taxonomicName id="2A57A1939F6D7858EA179D8D2EFA9E51" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="3AF90BD02F113A2065F750F90F601158" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fenzl. 
<bibRefCitation id="278ECAB9A1FBDCD663D071261C649F9A" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="6. Izdatel'stvo Akademii Nauk USSR, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B57" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1976. Taxonomic literature (ed. 2),Vol. 1. Scheltema, Bohn and Utrecht, Holkema, 1-1136." title="Taxonomic literature (ed. 2), Vol. 1. Scheltema, Bohn and Utrecht, Holkema, 1 - 1136." year="1976">Stafleu and Cowan (1976)</bibRefCitation>
stated 1843 as the true publication year for the first part of 
<normalizedToken id="9EF854C0BF47B12CCC82710A5FD9FA2F" originalValue="Boissier’s">Boissier's</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="AB25FED68E57DF3A1E42CF711658541D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnoses plantarum Orientalum novarum</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="CF37040EEFFCEEEBB54E1F58F8276907" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4109339" author="Burtt, BL" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="333 - 352" refId="B9" refString="Burtt, BL, Lewis, P, 1952. On the Flora of Kuweit: II. Kew Bulletin 7 (3): 333 - 352, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4109339" title="On the Flora of Kuweit: II." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4109339" volume="7" year="1952">Burtt and Lewis (1952)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that Rohrbach described 
<taxonomicName id="BBE6E5073D27D70ED1DAE2BCFD685DCD" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="D3AAA0C4AA4CCCD91E4E324AA3496C9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having glabrous petal claws, not ciliate as the taxon dealt with here. The type specimen for 
<taxonomicName id="5DA2F38696BC953C026F99645E299C7B" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="9717C2ADC9C426C979FF67FF0DED468C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fenzl was collected in an area that nowadays belongs to Turkey, at the mouth of the river Nahr al-Asi (also known as Orontis/Orontes), probably near Samandagi (old name 
<normalizedToken id="AAAF4E6F9E5DEBCDC06E8B2B177BC6E1" originalValue="Süveydiye">Sueveydiye</normalizedToken>
, probably the same as Svedie). There are collections from this area (
<emphasis id="C325AD9B00D445B473BF4AB61E2731FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haradjian 3069</emphasis>
in G, 
<emphasis id="A6B6E8CD8DEBC302FE0DA80A6AB191C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pabot s.n.</emphasis>
in G, 
<emphasis id="6A408C294FFB7E058C07BDFE41FEAF68" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mouterde V 58</emphasis>
in G, 
<emphasis id="21253BB30244AD44538371448B5ED789" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haradjian 1480</emphasis>
in E, 
<emphasis id="8C25D73631FAD28593AA5E6BCAF719BD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Davis</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="E83D70A6270C91A62140ECE50B9B4D79" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dodds &amp; Cetik 19551</emphasis>
in C) that clearly belong to this taxon. The type locality for 
<taxonomicName id="5321DB5B3EB30835116D6074336E7C30" genus="S." lsidName="S. cassia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cassia">
<emphasis id="5BEF40718733E34F25E180E975CA3614" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cassia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss. is also found in this area. We therefore follow 
<bibRefCitation id="C3764E467AB88D6AA72CE4688A912ED4" author="Melzheimer, V" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="341 - 508" refId="B35" refString="Melzheimer, V, 1988. Silene L. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora des iranischen hochlandes und der umrahmenden Gebirge (Persien, Afghanistan, Teile von West-Pakistan, Nord-Iraq, Azerbaidjan, Turkmenistan)): Caryophyllaceae II, Vol. 163. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 341 - 508" title="Silene L." volumeTitle="Flora des iranischen hochlandes und der umrahmenden Gebirge (Persien, Afghanistan, Teile von West-Pakistan, Nord-Iraq, Azerbaidjan, Turkmenistan )): Caryophyllaceae II, Vol." year="1988">Melzheimer (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and use the name 
<taxonomicName id="DBED0E2B57AD28B0CE21B6DA53AE0FE0" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="34A4555F4D9594FFE81FA6AE2B48E646" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fenzl for this taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B93594C4C4B732BA0EC4765549A6A90" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The 
<taxonomicName id="BFBCAF77D10F61B9B4A42301F3E9C5F4" authority="subsp. microsperma" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma subsp. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subSpecies" species="microsperma" subSpecies="microsperma">S. microsperma subsp. microsperma</taxonomicName>
accessions form a subclade in the 
<taxonomicName id="8F65B14E5A17A27D22C39DED55D5B727" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="354DEAFD25DE42C254AF2C4F70FB452D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade in the 
<emphasis id="BF774FC47DBB99E617044195C85AA619" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">RPB2</emphasis>
phylogeny (PP = 0.96, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8B78C91FBE9804C4C62CEB7BF65FC774" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Phylogenetic tree resulting from Bayesian analysis of the RPB 2 sequences including 76 taxa. The trees were summarized in a 50 % majority-rule consensus tree with the posterior probabilities (PP) indicated above branches. Bootstrap support values (&gt; 75 %) based on MP and ML are noted below branches, respectively. The numbers following the taxonomic name indicate the specimen ID and Genbank numbers (Suppl. material 1), respectively." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.159.51500.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447289" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
